Congressman Holding honored Bunn High School Football Coach David Howle

This afternoon, the House, with my support, rejected the U.N. Security Council’s anti-Israel Resolution which undermines the prospect for a sustainable peace agreement in the region. Israel is our strongest ally in the Middle East, and I firmly stand behind it.
Congressman Holding opposes the U.N. Security Council's anti-Israel resolution
Today we remember the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.
NA

The peaceful transfer of power today, as the 45th President of the United States is sworn into office, is something to celebrate. I look forward to working with the new Administration, as well as my colleagues in Congress, to get our country back on track.
Honoring the life of John Albert McNeill, Sr.

Yesterday, President Trump signed an executive order allowing the Keystone XL pipeline and the Dakota Access pipeline to go forward – getting thousands of people back to work while also strengthening our energy supply.
The National Research Program at the IRS turns taxpayers, chosen at random, into audit "guinea pigs."
NA
I was saddened to learn C.A. Dillon passed away -- he'll always be remembered as the "soul of Reynolds Coliseum."
Happy Presidents' Day -- today we celebrate President Washington's birthday. This photo was taken on May 31, 1932 as Washington's likeness was sculpted onto Mount Rushmore.

I am committed to being on the front lines of creating a simplified tax code that lowers the tax rate for hardworking Americans, encourages people to start a business in the United States, and creates more jobs for North Carolinians.

President Trump’s budget proposes cuts in U.N. funding and cuts in spending by the State Department. Both make sense. I don’t agree with everything the President proposes. But he’s started the debate and spending cuts are long past due.
Another reminder the threat of terrorism is real.
Had a great time discussing policy with the National Restaurant Association in Raleigh yesterday!

I am pleased to announce that my office will participate in the 2017 Congressional Art Competition. Students have until April 28th to submit their art to my office -- you can find the rules and guidelines on my website.

Yesterday afternoon, the House passed a trillion dollar spending bill. I believe taxpayers deserve better -- that we need to get our spending under control and our fiscal priorities in check -- which is why I voted against it.

Curbing North Korea's missile and nuclear program is paramount to national security, which is why the House, with my support, just passed new sanctions on North Korea's economy by targeting the institutions working with the Kim regime.
Had a great time yesterday travelling around Harnett County meeting with the Dunn Chamber of Commerce, Saab Barracuda, and Esterline!
Congratulations to 10th grader Jessie from Clayton, my 2017 Congressional Art Competition winner! Her drawing is entitled “Family Barn” and will be hanging in the United States Capitol all year.
Special thanks to my wife Lucy on this Mother's Day for being such a wonderful mother to our four children.
My thoughts and prayers are with Sen. Thom Tillis and his family this morning.
My family extends our prayers to the victims of this senseless act in Manchester. The U.S. stands absolute with the U.K.

The United States stands ready to assist the United Kingdom to bring those responsible for this heinous terrorist attack to justice. Congress will continue to support our colleagues in Parliament as they console a grieving nation and take the necessary steps to defend their homeland.
Please join me in remembering and honoring those who sacrificed their lives in service to our country this Memorial Day.

This is the third major terrorist attack in Great Britain in the last three months. These attacks point to the fragility of our own defense against ISIS and the fact that we have not defeated terrorism.
73 years ago today, more than 160,000 allied troops landed on the beaches of Normandy to liberate Europe. Their sacrifice is not forgotten.
Congratulations to former intern Kyle Anthony for receiving the Senior Medallion Award at UNC-W!

Praying for a speedy recovery for Rep. Steve Scalise and everyone injured in the shooting this morning. The Capitol Police, and all our first responders, deserve praise for the job they do each and every day.
Wishing everyone a safe and happy Independence Day!

In 2015, Kate Steinle was murdered in San Francisco by an illegal immigrant who had been deported multiple times. Last week, the House, with my support, passed “Kate’s Law” to  raise the maximum prison penalties for immigrants caught repeatedly entering the U.S. illegally.

According to the National Human Trafficking Hotline, North Carolina ranks among the top ten states across the country in the number of reported human trafficking cases. Yesterday afternoon, the House acted to fight back against human trafficking in order to help victims and give law enforcement the tools they need to stop these crimes.

I'm committed to being on the front lines of creating a simplified tax code that lowers the tax rate for hard-working Americans, encourages people to start a business, and creates more jobs for North Carolinians.
NA
Praying for all of those hurt in Charlottesville. All Americans must come together against racism and hatred, which have no place in our society.
I had a great time last week touring facilities and meeting with folks in the district!
Thank you to everyone who hosted me last week in the district!

Please join me in remembering those who lost their lives on September 11, 2001. We must never forget.
The House, with my support, passed a bill today aimed at keeping illegal immigrant gang members out of the United States.
My prayers are with all of the victims and their families this morning in Las Vegas. Our first responders who put themselves in harm’s way to protect others deserve our thanks.
I met some great folks last week in the district. Thank you for having me!

The House, with my support, voted this morning to expand sanctions on Iran to stop their ballistic missile program. Yesterday, the House voted to stop Iran's flow of money to Hezbollah. We need to use all appropriate means to stop their weapons programs and cutoff their funding for terrorism.

Today the Ways and Means Committee voted to reform our tax code for the first time in over 30 years. Cutting taxes will grow our economy, ensuring the United States is on a level playing field with the rest of the world.

On this Veterans Day, I'm grateful so many risked their lives to protect our freedom. Thank you for your service.  The Library of Congress is compiling stories from veterans of every generation. If you or a family member would like to share, click the link below.

This afternoon the House voted to reform our tax system. Our goal is to grow our economy and ensure that businesses of all sizes have the capital necessary to hire more employees, grow their operations, and finally give American workers the raise they deserve.
This Thanksgiving, I’m thankful for all the men and women serving overseas who are unable to be with their families. Thank you for protecting our freedom and Happy Thanksgiving.
Seventy-six years ago today, the United States was attacked at Pearl Harbor. We must never forget the thousands of American causalities lost December 7, 1941 – "a date which will live in infamy."

The House voted to reform our tax system this afternoon. Cutting taxes will grow our economy and ensure the United States is on a level playing field with the rest of the world.
Merry Christmas! Wishing everyone a blessed holiday season.   This photo of the White House Christmas tree was taken in 1934.
